        <title>Front Parking / Turn Signals - Bulb Replacement</title>
        <para>Follow procedure to remove and replace burned out parking light or directional light bulb:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove screws that secure turn signal lens assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Gently pull turn signal lens from light pod.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove light socket from turn signal lens assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bulb from socket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new bulb in socket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install light socket into turn signal assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position light assembly into light pod and install screws.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check light operation.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
